                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17170983" author="tilman" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2020 17:36:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That PDF uses 186 images of text instead of using text. These images have the /Interpolate flag set to &quot;false&quot;. However PDFBox only doesn&apos;t interpolate when the image is also scaled up (because of barcodes). Your PDF has many images of nominal size 2x2. But they have a mask that is bigger. So your images are considered to be scaled up but are not really. I did a quick test using the actual ARGB size and then your PDF renders nicely. I&apos;ll do some more tests to see how this works on other PDFs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17170992" author="dbalasub" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2020 17:54:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks a lot for the prompt response &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt;&#160;Appreciate it. So if I understand you are saying that you are going to do some testing with other PDFs before checking in the fix for this issue correct? Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17171015" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2020 18:14:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1880574 from Tilman Hausherr in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/2.0&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1880574&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1880574&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4930&quot; title=&quot;Font thickness issue when we use PDFBox for generating images from PDF&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4930&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-4930&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: we use the sizes of the ARGB image, these can be different than the original sizes of the base image, when the mask is bigger&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17171016" author="tilman" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2020 18:14:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah I did and the rendering of several files are improved. You can delete your files. The effect and the causes can also be seen in the original file of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4516&quot; title=&quot;PDFBox text and images are blurry even after rendering with high DPI&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4516&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-4516&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (which, coincidentally, is named &quot;original.pdf&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17171018" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2020 18:17:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1880575 from Tilman Hausherr in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/issue45&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1880575&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1880575&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4930&quot; title=&quot;Font thickness issue when we use PDFBox for generating images from PDF&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4930&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-4930&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: we use the sizes of the ARGB image, these can be different than the original sizes of the base image, when the mask is bigger&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17171019" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2020 18:17:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1880576 from Tilman Hausherr in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1880576&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1880576&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4930&quot; title=&quot;Font thickness issue when we use PDFBox for generating images from PDF&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4930&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-4930&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: we use the sizes of the ARGB image, these can be different than the original sizes of the base image, when the mask is bigger&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17171054" author="tilman" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2020 18:58:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Done. Thanks for the report. You can test a snapshot here&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://repository.apache.org/content/groups/snapshots/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfbox-app/2.0.21-SNAPSHOT/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://repository.apache.org/content/groups/snapshots/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfbox-app/2.0.21-SNAPSHOT/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17171056" author="dbalasub" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2020 19:00:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt;&#160;Thanks for making the fix in the snapshot version. However, my question is: Can I use the snapshot version for our production codebase? Please advice.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17171059" author="tilman" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2020 19:03:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Improved files:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;***PDF-775.pdf&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2128&quot; title=&quot;CMYK images are not supported correctly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2128&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2128&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;-573636.pdf, page 6 and 7 (dots smoother)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3546&quot; title=&quot;IOException over DataFormatException, &amp;quot;invalid stored block lengths&amp;quot; on a valid PDF&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-3546&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-3546&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.pdf, page 3 and 4 (dots smoother)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4137&quot; title=&quot;Allow subsampled/downscaled rendering of images, and rendering subimages &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4137&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-4137&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;-067445-JPX-p3.pdf (text smoother)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4516&quot; title=&quot;PDFBox text and images are blurry even after rendering with high DPI&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4516&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-4516&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.pdf (text smoother)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3558&quot; title=&quot;NPE in JBig2Filter if BitsPerComponent is missing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-3558&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-3558&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.pdf (luratech logo smoother)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17171063" author="tilman" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2020 19:08:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can&apos;t decide for you but I&apos;d think yes. We just had our huge (250000 PDFs) text extraction regression test which resulted in a change related of exceptions with 3 pdfs but the tests haven&apos;t been repeated since then. The build tests and my own rendering tests (1000 PDFs) are fine.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17171068" author="dbalasub" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2020 19:13:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt;&#160;However would you have any idea when we will get the 2.0.21 version? Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17171072" author="tilman" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2020 19:24:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Should hopefully be within 1-2 weeks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17171074" author="dbalasub" created="Tue, 4 Aug 2020 19:26:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That is awesome &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt;&#160;That sounds great. In that case, we can wait for the 2.0.21 version. Thanks again for such a prompt response and action! You guys are great!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17180824" author="dbalasub" created="Wed, 19 Aug 2020 21:19:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hope you are doing great. I just want to check with you on the status of the 2.0.21 release. Please update me when you get a chance. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Dushyanth&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17180943" author="tilman" created="Thu, 20 Aug 2020 03:32:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The voting process started on monday evening. This takes 72 hours. All votes were positive until now. Thus I&apos;d expect the release to be thursday evening or friday morning / evening depending on time resources. The release candidate is at &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://dist.apache.org/repos/dist/dev/pdfbox/2.0.21/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://dist.apache.org/repos/dist/dev/pdfbox/2.0.21/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17181379" author="dbalasub" created="Thu, 20 Aug 2020 18:59:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt;&#160;This sounds good. I will wait for the 2.0.21 release. Thanks again for all your hard work!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17181505" author="dbalasub" created="Fri, 21 Aug 2020 00:27:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt;&#160;one more feedback which we got from our product manager is that the fonts are definitely more clear now than before but it is not as crisp as the original pdf. Is there more room for improvement in this aspect? Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17181655" author="tilman" created="Fri, 21 Aug 2020 06:44:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With &quot;as the original pdf&quot; the PM probably means &quot;Adobe Reader&quot;. They&apos;re the gold standard, but IMHO the difference is minimal. The difficulties of doing a rendering is best described in this video: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TiqDqd-1pwU&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TiqDqd-1pwU&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;br/&gt;
Adobe also does a better job at interpolation than the java graphics engine. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17182065" author="dbalasub" created="Fri, 21 Aug 2020 18:30:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the response &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
